> Top News Democrats bring gun debate back to presidential campaign In this Oct. 13, 2015, photo, Democratic presidential candidate Hillary Rodham Clinton speaks during the Democratic presidential debate in Las Vegas. It seems like there was a 15-year virtual gag order on guns in presidential politics. But Democrats are talking again about the issue. President Barack Obama is considering taking more executive action. Clinton says she’s had "enough" of the legislative stalemate on guns. (AP Photo/John Locher) 
